	<p>
	Off-campus education courses satisfy residency requirements and are offered in various communities for the student's convenience.  Degree programs at the master's, educational specialist, and doctoral levels are available through the UIB.  Persons interested in pursuing an Ed.D. or Ph.D. in Education with an emphasis in Educational Administration, Adult Education, or Vocational Education may complete their residency requirements at the UIB.  The division of Adult, Counselor and Technology Education offers a B.S. degree in Vocational Education.  Certification requirements may be completed in Vocational Education, Educational Administration, and in Special Educational Administration.</font></td>
